gomodel:SYNGO_945  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099026 replaced by GO:0042734" , "Rationale: Fig 3, 5: The parallel fibers and presynaptic varicosities in the molecular layer of cerebellum were stained in EM of 10-day old mouse.\nFig 6: In the internal granular cell layer of the cerebellum, the mossy fiber terminals are stained\n\nNote that other neuron types exhibit postsynaptic labeling (annotation 946), but that at no synapse both pre- and post-synaptic labeling was detected.\n\n12/10/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known lipid anchor of the protein, the \"anchored component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Mice 1, 5, and 10 d of age were killed by decapitation or intracardiac perfusion." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0912-1514" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3670-7863" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
